    \"text\": \"“Speculative Speculative Decoding” Even though speculative decoding speed up LLM inference, it still has a hidden “stop-and-wait” step, where the draft model can’t start the next guess until the big model finishes verifying the last one. This paper fixes that by making drafting and verification run in parallel. The draft model precomputes speculations for the most likely verification outcomes while verification is happening, so when the outcome lands, the next tokens are ready instantly. This cuts the overhead and delivering up to ~2x faster than optimized speculative decoding and ~5x over plain autoregressive decoding!\"
